mcmVNETChCfgTable.name: mcmVNETChCfgTable
mcmVNETChCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Channel Configuration table. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETChCfgEntry.name: mcmVNETChCfgEntry
mcmVNETChCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Channel Configuration \ table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChCfgLimID.name: mcmVNETChCfgLimID
mcmVNETChCfgLimID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The card lim (logical interface module) number of a \ particular voice channel. Used as an index to the \ VNET Voice Channel Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChCfgChannelID.name: mcmVNETChCfgChannelID
mcmVNETChCfgChannelID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The position of the voice channel in the lim. \ Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Channel Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChCfgVoiceProfile.name: mcmVNETChCfgVoiceProfile
mcmVNETChCfgVoiceProfile.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ to be used to configure the specified voice \ channel. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChCfgSwitchingProfile.name: mcmVNETChCfgSwitchingProfile
mcmVNETChCfgSwitchingProfile.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ to be used for a switching call. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChCfgInterfaceType.name: mcmVNETChCfgInterfaceType
mcmVNETChCfgInterfaceType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the interface \ type of the specified voice channel. (Operational); HELP = Upon powerup, the interface type will not be \ available until the DSP software is loaded and its \ status is reported.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgTable.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgTable
mcmVNETProfileCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Profile Configuration table. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEntry.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEntry
mcmVNETProfileCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Profile Configuration \ table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgProfileNum.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgProfileNum
mcmVNETProfileCfgProfileNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ number. Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Profile Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgMode.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgMode
mcmVNETProfileCfgMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel signal processing. (Operational); HELP = Can be used to set to either dual mode with \ both voice and fax, or just voice.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDigitizingRate.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDigitizingRate
mcmVNETProfileCfgDigitizingRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ digitizing algorithm. (Operational); HELP = Rate at which voice is digitized in \ designated in bits per second.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgInputLevelGain.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgInputLevelGain
mcmVNETProfileCfgInputLevelGain.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the input \ signal gain in dB. (Operational); HELP = For DVM, max value is 8 dB. If more than \ 8 dB is configured, 8 dB will be used. \ The range for the BRI card is -15 to 15 dB.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgOutputLevelAttn.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgOutputLevelAttn
mcmVNETProfileCfgOutputLevelAttn.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the output \ signal attenuation in dB. (Operational); HELP = For DVM, max value is 8 dB. If more than \ 8 dB is configured, 8 dB will be used. \ The range for the BRI card is -15 to 15dB.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgBusyOutMode.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgBusyOutMode
mcmVNETProfileCfgBusyOutMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel busy out control type. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgBandwidth.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgBandwidth
mcmVNETProfileCfgBandwidth.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel link bandwidth reservation style. \ (Operational); HELP = 2 is used for forced connects or PVCs only. \ 1 is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgBackground.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgBackground
mcmVNETProfileCfgBackground.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel background noise generation type. \ (Operational); HELP = The ability of passing background noise or \ silencing the channel during idle periods. \ First option allows the background noise to be \ regenerated during the periods, whereas the \ second option suppresses background noise during \ idle periods.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgBRIPulseRate.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgBRIPulseRate
mcmVNETProfileCfgBRIPulseRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel pulse rate in pulses per second. \ (Operational); HELP = NOTE: This object is used by the Partner card \ and not for the ISDN BRI voice card.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEMSigFormat.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEMSigFormat
mcmVNETProfileCfgEMSigFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel E&M signaling format. (Operational); HELP = 2 and 3 are used for force connects only. \ 1 (DC) is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgFXSSigFormat.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgFXSSigFormat
mcmVNETProfileCfgFXSSigFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel FXS signaling format. (Operational); HELP = 1 is used for force connects only. \ 2 is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDVMSigFormat.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDVMSigFormat
mcmVNETProfileCfgDVMSigFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel DVM signaling format. (Operational); HELP = 3 and 4 are used for force connects only. \ 1 is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgNumberOfRings.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgNumberOfRings
mcmVNETProfileCfgNumberOfRings.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies when the \ voice channel (FXO or 3-port) will answer \ the call request. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEMAnalOper.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEMAnalOper
mcmVNETProfileCfgEMAnalOper.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the E&M \ voice channel operation as either 2 or 4 wire \ operation. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgRingingFreq.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgRingingFreq
mcmVNETProfileCfgRingingFreq.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel (FXS or 3-port) ringing frequency. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgFaxDigRate.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgFaxDigRate
mcmVNETProfileCfgFaxDigRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel Fax digitizing rate in bits per second. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDiscSupervision.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDiscSupervision
mcmVNETProfileCfgDiscSupervision.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel method to detect the line disconnect. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgLineImpedance.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgLineImpedance
mcmVNETProfileCfgLineImpedance.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel type of line impedance. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgMaxOutputLevel.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgMaxOutputLevel
mcmVNETProfileCfgMaxOutputLevel.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel maximum output level. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgRegenDelay.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgRegenDelay
mcmVNETProfileCfgRegenDelay.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel time (in seconds) to delay before dialing \ out the number (i.e., time to wait for dial tone). \ (Operational); HELP = NOTE: This object is not required for the ISDN BRI \ voice card; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDialDigTimeLimit.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDialDigTimeLimit
mcmVNETProfileCfgDialDigTimeLimit.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel inter-digit time-out time (in seconds). \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgMaxNumForDig.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgMaxNumForDig
mcmVNETProfileCfgMaxNumForDig.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel maximum number of digits that can \ be dialed. (Operational); HELP = 0 is used for auto-call functionality.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgRegenFormat.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgRegenFormat
mcmVNETProfileCfgRegenFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel dial digit regeneration format. \ (Operational); HELP = NOTE: This object is not required for the ISDN \ BRI voice card.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgCallProgTone.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgCallProgTone
mcmVNETProfileCfgCallProgTone.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel call progress tone required for different \ countries or areas. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDTMFDetector.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDTMFDetector
mcmVNETProfileCfgDTMFDetector.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether to turn on or off the DTMF \ detector. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgJitters.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgJitters
mcmVNETProfileCfgJitters.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel maximum jitters delay (in milliseconds). \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEchoCanceller.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEchoCanceller
mcmVNETProfileCfgEchoCanceller.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether to turn on or off the echo \ canceller. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgAutoGainControl.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgAutoGainControl
mcmVNETProfileCfgAutoGainControl.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether to automatically set the input \ signal level. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgCompanderFormat.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgCompanderFormat
mcmVNETProfileCfgCompanderFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel (DVM or BRI) compander type. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgPremiumVoice.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgPremiumVoice
mcmVNETProfileCfgPremiumVoice.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel (DVM) whether to enable or disable the \ transparent voice (no compression) algorithm. \ (Operational); HELP = This object is also used by the ISDN BRI voice card \ to enable/disable Digital Lossless Switching Pattern \ Generation and Pattern Search.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEndOfDialChar.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEndOfDialChar
mcmVNETProfileCfgEndOfDialChar.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether '#' is used to end a dialing input. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgBckGrndNoiseLevel.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgBckGrndNoiseLevel
mcmVNETProfileCfgBckGrndNoiseLevel.description: NAME = ; DESC = Signal input above this level is considered\ a voiced signal, below this level, the \ Voice Activity Detector (VAD), will \ determine if it is a voiced signal or \ background noise. (Operational); HELP = Refer to the International \ Telecommunication Union(ITU-T) G.711 \ document for more information; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgSilenceHngOvrTime.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgSilenceHngOvrTime
mcmVNETProfileCfgSilenceHngOvrTime.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates the time delay to switch \ from voice to silence.\ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgIdlePattern.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgIdlePattern
mcmVNETProfileCfgIdlePattern.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object represents the \ Idle pattern on the line when no call is up.\ Specific to a PBX. This is a permanent DSP \ configuration parameter; HELP = This value can be used to detect that a call \ has finished and that the echo canceller should \ be reset and that fax mode should be terminated.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEcanFilterLength.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEcanFilterLength
mcmVNETProfileCfgEcanFilterLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the filter \ length for echo canceller. This is a permanent \ DSP configuration parameter.; HELP = A length of 128 is equal to 16ms.\ A length of 256 is equal to 32ms.; -- NOTE: The ISDN BRI voice card supports 32ms only; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgEcanErlImprovement.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgEcanErlImprovement
mcmVNETProfileCfgEcanErlImprovement.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object is used for echo \ canceller Er1 improvement. This is a DSP \ Dynamic configuration parameter. \ A signal will be attenuated by this dB \ amount before being passed through the \ echo canceller. After the echo canceller, \ it will be amplified by this same dB amount, \ for a net gain of 0 dB. \ This attenuation amplicfication cycle reduces \ the resolution of the signal ( -18 ..0 ).; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgNoiseFloorOffset.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgNoiseFloorOffset
mcmVNETProfileCfgNoiseFloorOffset.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object will suppress the \ impulsive backround noise in order to achieve \ silence suppression savings. HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDtmfGenBurstLength.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDtmfGenBurstLength
mcmVNETProfileCfgDtmfGenBurstLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = DTMF burst generation in milliseconds.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETProfileCfgDtmRegenBurstLength.name: mcmVNETProfileCfgDtmRegenBurstLength
mcmVNETProfileCfgDtmRegenBurstLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = DTMF burst Regeneration length in milliseconds.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgTable.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgTable
mcmVNETSwProfCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Switching Profile Configuration \ table.(Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgEntry.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgEntry
mcmVNETSwProfCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Switching Profile \ Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgProfileNum.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgProfileNum
mcmVNETSwProfCfgProfileNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ number. Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Switching Profile Configuration table. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallRestrict.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallRestrict
mcmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallRestrict.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies how to \ handle outgoing calls for voice channel \ switching. (Operational); HELP = 2: include CUG ID in outgoing call. \ 3: include restriction class in outgoing call. \ 4: include both CUG ID and restriction \ class in outgoing call. \ 5: outgoing call is not allowed.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgInCallRestrict.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgInCallRestrict
mcmVNETSwProfCfgInCallRestrict.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies how to \ handle incoming calls for voice channel \ switching. (Operational); HELP = 2: check CUG ID in incoming call. (Must \ match our CUG ID for call acceptance. \ 3: check RCC in incoming call. (Must be \ greater than or equal to our RCC for call \ acceptance. \ 4: check both CUG and RCC in incoming \ call. \ 5: incoming call is not allowed.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgCUGID.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgCUGID
mcmVNETSwProfCfgCUGID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object assigns the Closed \ User Group ID for a voice channel. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgRestrictClassCd.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgRestrictClassCd
mcmVNETSwProfCfgRestrictClassCd.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object assigns the Restriction \ Class Code for a voice channel. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallEntNum.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallEntNum
mcmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallEntNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object provides a voice \ channel Auto Call destination number by \ specifying an index into the ingress table. \ (Operational); HELP = 0: auto call disabled. \ 1-32: index to the ingress table entry where \ the dial number is specified. \ The auto call for the ISDN BRI voice card is \ always disabled.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgCallNegStrategy.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgCallNegStrategy
mcmVNETSwProfCfgCallNegStrategy.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the preference \ for the voice algorithm when an outgoing call is \ made. (Operational); HELP = specific: whatever is configured. \ bandwidth: bigger block size. \ delay: shorter block size.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgTransmitPriority.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgTransmitPriority
mcmVNETSwProfCfgTransmitPriority.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object assigns the priority \ of the voice data to be transmitted. (Operational); HELP = 0: lowest priority. \ 15: highest priority.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallType.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallType
mcmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallType.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates the type of auto-call \ switching to be performed by the \ voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgAddServerSelect.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgAddServerSelect
mcmVNETSwProfCfgAddServerSelect.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates which DNA server is used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallMode.name: mcmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallMode
mcmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates the type of call being made.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETIngressDigFilterTable.name: mcmVNETIngressDigFilterTable
mcmVNETIngressDigFilterTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Ingress Digit Filtering \ Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETIngressDigFilterEntry.name: mcmVNETIngressDigFilterEntry
mcmVNETIngressDigFilterEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Ingress Digit \ Filtering Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETIngressDigFilterIndex.name: mcmVNETIngressDigFilterIndex
mcmVNETIngressDigFilterIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the index to \ the ingress table. Used as an index to the VNET \ Voice Ingress Digit Filtering Configuration table. \ Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETIngressDigFilterIngressNum.name: mcmVNETIngressDigFilterIngressNum
mcmVNETIngressDigFilterIngressNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the digit \ pattern to be matched. (Null terminated \ character string.) (Operational); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', \ '*', '+', '[' and ']' .; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETIngressDigFilterManipString.name: mcmVNETIngressDigFilterManipString
mcmVNETIngressDigFilterManipString.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects commands \ to produce the ingress digits for speed dial, \ call redirect, and source ID insertion features. \ (Operational); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', \ '*', 'D', and 'I'.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETEgressDigManipTable.name: mcmVNETEgressDigManipTable
mcmVNETEgressDigManipTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Egress Digit Manipulation \ Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETEgressDigManipEntry.name: mcmVNETEgressDigManipEntry
mcmVNETEgressDigManipEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Egress Digit \ Manipulation Configuration table. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETEgressDigManipIndex.name: mcmVNETEgressDigManipIndex
mcmVNETEgressDigManipIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the index to \ the egress table. Used as an index to the VNET \ Voice Egress Digit Manipulation Configuration \ table. Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETEgressDigManipPhoneNum.name: mcmVNETEgressDigManipPhoneNum
mcmVNETEgressDigManipPhoneNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the phone \ number that voice channels are associated with. \ This is the number to be registered to the Address \ Server (RSA). (Operational); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', and '*'.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETEgressDigManipString.name: mcmVNETEgressDigManipString
mcmVNETEgressDigManipString.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects commands \ to produce the egress digits for FXO, E&M, \ or FXS 3-Port interface. The result is the \ number to be sent to the connected phone \ device. (Operational); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', '*', \ '+', 'D', 'H', and 'I'. The character 'H' is used \ used to trigger immediate dial handling by the PBX.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETEgressDigManipChIDList.name: mcmVNETEgressDigManipChIDList
mcmVNETEgressDigManipChIDList.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects voice channels \ associated with the phone number. The valid \ string consists of the substring 'B1'~'B6', \ 'C1'~'C12', 'D1'~'D12', and 'E1'~'E2'. \ (Operational); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, 'B', 'C', \ 'D', and 'E'.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETChCfgTable.name: nvmVNETChCfgTable
nvmVNETChCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Channel Configuration table. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

nvmVNETChCfgEntry.name: nvmVNETChCfgEntry
nvmVNETChCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Channel Configuration \ table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETChCfgLimID.name: nvmVNETChCfgLimID
nvmVNETChCfgLimID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The card lim (logical interface module) number of a \ particular voice channel. Used as an index to the \ VNET Voice Channel Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETChCfgChannelID.name: nvmVNETChCfgChannelID
nvmVNETChCfgChannelID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The position of the voice channel in the lim. \ Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Channel Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETChCfgVoiceProfile.name: nvmVNETChCfgVoiceProfile
nvmVNETChCfgVoiceProfile.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ to be used to configure the specified voice \ channel. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETChCfgSwitchingProfile.name: nvmVNETChCfgSwitchingProfile
nvmVNETChCfgSwitchingProfile.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ to be used for a switching call. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETChCfgInterfaceType.name: nvmVNETChCfgInterfaceType
nvmVNETChCfgInterfaceType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the interface \ type of the specified voice channel. (Configuration); HELP = Upon powerup, the interface type will not be \ available until the DSP software is loaded and its \ status is reported.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgTable.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgTable
nvmVNETProfileCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Profile Configuration table. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEntry.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEntry
nvmVNETProfileCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Profile Configuration \ table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgProfileNum.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgProfileNum
nvmVNETProfileCfgProfileNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ number. Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Profile Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgMode.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgMode
nvmVNETProfileCfgMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel signal processing. (Configuration); HELP = Can be used to set to either dual mode with \ both voice and fax, or just voice.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDigitizingRate.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDigitizingRate
nvmVNETProfileCfgDigitizingRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ digitizing algorithm. (Configuration); HELP = Rate at which voice is digitized in \ designated in bits per second.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgInputLevelGain.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgInputLevelGain
nvmVNETProfileCfgInputLevelGain.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the input \ signal gain in dB. (Configuration); HELP = For DVM, max value is 8 dB. If more than \ 8 dB is configured, 8 dB will be used.\ The ISDN BRI voice card range is -15 to 15dB.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgOutputLevelAttn.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgOutputLevelAttn
nvmVNETProfileCfgOutputLevelAttn.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the output \ signal attenuation in dB. (Configuration); HELP = For DVM, max value is 8 dB. If more than \ 8 dB is configured, 8 dB will be used.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgBusyOutMode.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgBusyOutMode
nvmVNETProfileCfgBusyOutMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel busy out control type. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgBandwidth.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgBandwidth
nvmVNETProfileCfgBandwidth.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel link bandwidth reservation style. \ (Configuration); HELP = 2 is used for forced connects or PVCs only. \ 1 is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgBackground.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgBackground
nvmVNETProfileCfgBackground.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel background noise generation type. \ (Configuration); HELP = The ability of passing background noise or \ silencing the channel during idle periods. \ First option allows the background noise to be \ regenerated during the periods, whereas the \ second option suppresses background noise during \ idle periods.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgBRIPulseRate.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgBRIPulseRate
nvmVNETProfileCfgBRIPulseRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel pulse rate in pulses per second. \ (Configuration); HELP = NOTE: This object is used by the Partner Card, \ not by the ISDN BRI voice card.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEMSigFormat.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEMSigFormat
nvmVNETProfileCfgEMSigFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel E&M signaling format. (Configuration); HELP = 2 and 3 are used for force connects only. \ 1 (DC) is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgFXSSigFormat.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgFXSSigFormat
nvmVNETProfileCfgFXSSigFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel FXS signaling format. (Configuration); HELP = 1 is used for force connects only. \ 2 is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDVMSigFormat.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDVMSigFormat
nvmVNETProfileCfgDVMSigFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel DVM signaling format. (Configuration); HELP = 3 and 4 are used for force connects only. \ 1 is used for switched connects.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgNumberOfRings.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgNumberOfRings
nvmVNETProfileCfgNumberOfRings.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies when the \ voice channel (FXO or 3-port) will answer \ the call request. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEMAnalOper.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEMAnalOper
nvmVNETProfileCfgEMAnalOper.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the E&M \ voice channel operation as either 2 or 4 wire \ operation. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgRingingFreq.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgRingingFreq
nvmVNETProfileCfgRingingFreq.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel (FXS or 3-port) ringing frequency. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgFaxDigRate.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgFaxDigRate
nvmVNETProfileCfgFaxDigRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel Fax digitizing rate in bits per second. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDiscSupervision.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDiscSupervision
nvmVNETProfileCfgDiscSupervision.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel method to detect the line disconnect. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgLineImpedance.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgLineImpedance
nvmVNETProfileCfgLineImpedance.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the voice \ channel type of line impedance. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgMaxOutputLevel.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgMaxOutputLevel
nvmVNETProfileCfgMaxOutputLevel.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel maximum output level. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgRegenDelay.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgRegenDelay
nvmVNETProfileCfgRegenDelay.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel time (in seconds) to delay before dialing \ out the number (i.e., time to wait for dial tone). \ (Configuration); HELP = NOTE : This object is not used for the ISDN BRI \ voice card.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDialDigTimeLimit.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDialDigTimeLimit
nvmVNETProfileCfgDialDigTimeLimit.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel inter-digit time-out time (in seconds). \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgMaxNumForDig.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgMaxNumForDig
nvmVNETProfileCfgMaxNumForDig.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel maximum number of digits that can \ be dialed. (Configuration); HELP = 0 is used for auto-call functionality.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgRegenFormat.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgRegenFormat
nvmVNETProfileCfgRegenFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel dial digit regeneration format. \ (Configuration); HELP = NOTE: THIS object is not used for the ISDN \ BRI voice card.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgCallProgTone.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgCallProgTone
nvmVNETProfileCfgCallProgTone.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel call progress tone required for different \ countries or areas. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDTMFDetector.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDTMFDetector
nvmVNETProfileCfgDTMFDetector.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether to turn on or off the DTMF \ detector. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgJitters.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgJitters
nvmVNETProfileCfgJitters.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel maximum jitters delay (in milliseconds). \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEchoCanceller.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEchoCanceller
nvmVNETProfileCfgEchoCanceller.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether to turn on or off the echo \ canceller. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgAutoGainControl.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgAutoGainControl
nvmVNETProfileCfgAutoGainControl.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether to automatically set the input \ signal level. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgCompanderFormat.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgCompanderFormat
nvmVNETProfileCfgCompanderFormat.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the voice \ channel (DVM or BRI) compander type. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgPremiumVoice.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgPremiumVoice
nvmVNETProfileCfgPremiumVoice.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel (DVM) whether to enable or disable the \ transparent voice (no compression) algorithm. \ (Configuration); HELP = This object is also used by the ISDN BRI voice \ card to enable/disable Digital Lossless Switching \ Pattern Generation and Pattern Search.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEndOfDialChar.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEndOfDialChar
nvmVNETProfileCfgEndOfDialChar.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies to the voice \ channel whether '#' is used to end a dialing input. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgBckGrndNoiseLevel.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgBckGrndNoiseLevel
nvmVNETProfileCfgBckGrndNoiseLevel.description: NAME = ; DESC = Signal input above this level is considered\ a voiced signal, below this level, the \ Voice Activity Detector (VAD), will \ determine if it is a voiced signal or \ background noise. (Configuration); HELP = Refer to the International \ Telecommunication Union(ITU-T) G.711 \ document for more information; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgSilenceHngOvrTime.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgSilenceHngOvrTime
nvmVNETProfileCfgSilenceHngOvrTime.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates the time delay to switch \ from voice to silence.\ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgIdlePattern.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgIdlePattern
nvmVNETProfileCfgIdlePattern.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object represents the \ Idle pattern on the line when no call is up.\ Specific to a PBX. This is a permanent DSP \ configuration parameter; HELP = This value can be used to detect that a call \ has finished and that the echo canceller should \ be reset and that fax mode should be terminated.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEcanFilterLength.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEcanFilterLength
nvmVNETProfileCfgEcanFilterLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the filter \ length for echo canceller. This is a permanent \ DSP configuration parameter.; HELP = A length of 128 is equal to 16ms.\ A length of 256 is equal to 32ms.; ---- NOTE: The ISDN BRI voice card supports 32ms only; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgEcanErlImprovement.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgEcanErlImprovement
nvmVNETProfileCfgEcanErlImprovement.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object is used for echo \ canceller Er1 improvement. This is a DSP \ Dynamic configuration parameter. \ A signal will be attenuated by this dB \ amount before being passed through the \ echo canceller. After the echo canceller, \ it will be amplified by this same dB amount, \ for a net gain of 0 dB. \ This attenuation amplicfication cycle reduces \ the resolution of the signal ( -18 ..0 ).; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgNoiseFloorOffset.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgNoiseFloorOffset
nvmVNETProfileCfgNoiseFloorOffset.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object will suppress the \ impulsive backround noise in order to achieve \ silence suppression savings. HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDtmfGenBurstLength.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDtmfGenBurstLength
nvmVNETProfileCfgDtmfGenBurstLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = DTMF burst generation in milliseconds.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETProfileCfgDtmRegenBurstLength.name: nvmVNETProfileCfgDtmRegenBurstLength
nvmVNETProfileCfgDtmRegenBurstLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = DTMF burst Regeneration length in milliseconds.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgTable.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgTable
nvmVNETSwProfCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Switching Profile Configuration \ table.(Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgEntry.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgEntry
nvmVNETSwProfCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Switching Profile \ Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgProfileNum.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgProfileNum
nvmVNETSwProfCfgProfileNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the profile \ number. Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Switching Profile Configuration table. \ (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallRestrict.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallRestrict
nvmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallRestrict.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies how to \ handle outgoing calls for voice channel \ switching. (Configuration); HELP = 2: include CUG ID in outgoing call. \ 3: include restriction class in outgoing call. \ 4: include both CUG ID and restriction \ class in outgoing call. \ 5: outgoing call is not allowed.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgInCallRestrict.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgInCallRestrict
nvmVNETSwProfCfgInCallRestrict.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies how to \ handle incoming calls for voice channel \ switching. (Configuration); HELP = 2: check CUG ID in incoming call. (Must \ match our CUG ID for call acceptance. \ 3: check RCC in incoming call. (Must be \ greater than or equal to our RCC for call \ acceptance. \ 4: check both CUG and RCC in incoming \ call. \ 5: incoming call is not allowed.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgCUGID.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgCUGID
nvmVNETSwProfCfgCUGID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object assigns the Closed \ User Group ID for a voice channel. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgRestrictClassCd.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgRestrictClassCd
nvmVNETSwProfCfgRestrictClassCd.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object assigns the Restriction \ Class Code for a voice channel. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallEntNum.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallEntNum
nvmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallEntNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object provides a voice \ channel Auto Call destination number by \ specifying an index into the ingress table. \ (Configuration); HELP = 0: auto call disabled. \ 1-32: index to the ingress table entry where \ the dial number is specified. \ The auto call for the ISDN BRI voice card is always \ disabled.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgCallNegStrategy.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgCallNegStrategy
nvmVNETSwProfCfgCallNegStrategy.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object specifies the preference \ for the voice algorithm when an outgoing call is \ made. (Configuration); HELP = specific: whatever is configured. \ bandwidth: bigger block size. \ delay: shorter block size.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgTransmitPriority.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgTransmitPriority
nvmVNETSwProfCfgTransmitPriority.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object assigns the priority \ of the voice data to be transmitted. (Configuration); HELP = 0: lowest priority. \ 15: highest priority.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallType.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallType
nvmVNETSwProfCfgAutoCallType.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates the type of auto-call \ switching to be performed by the \ voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgAddServerSelect.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgAddServerSelect
nvmVNETSwProfCfgAddServerSelect.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates which DNA server is used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallMode.name: nvmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallMode
nvmVNETSwProfCfgOutCallMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = Indicates the type of call being made.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETIngressDigFilterTable.name: nvmVNETIngressDigFilterTable
nvmVNETIngressDigFilterTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Ingress Digit Filtering \ Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

nvmVNETIngressDigFilterEntry.name: nvmVNETIngressDigFilterEntry
nvmVNETIngressDigFilterEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Ingress Digit \ Filtering Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETIngressDigFilterIndex.name: nvmVNETIngressDigFilterIndex
nvmVNETIngressDigFilterIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the index to \ the ingress table. Used as an index to the VNET \ Voice Ingress Digit Filtering Configuration table. \ Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETIngressDigFilterIngressNum.name: nvmVNETIngressDigFilterIngressNum
nvmVNETIngressDigFilterIngressNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the digit \ pattern to be matched. (Null terminated \ character string.) (Configuration); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', \ '*', '+', '[' and ']' .; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETIngressDigFilterManipString.name: nvmVNETIngressDigFilterManipString
nvmVNETIngressDigFilterManipString.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects commands \ to produce the ingress digits for speed dial, \ call redirect, and source ID insertion features. \ (Configuration); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', \ '*', 'D', and 'I'.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETEgressDigManipTable.name: nvmVNETEgressDigManipTable
nvmVNETEgressDigManipTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Egress Digit Manipulation \ Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

nvmVNETEgressDigManipEntry.name: nvmVNETEgressDigManipEntry
nvmVNETEgressDigManipEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Egress Digit \ Manipulation Configuration table. (Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETEgressDigManipIndex.name: nvmVNETEgressDigManipIndex
nvmVNETEgressDigManipIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the index to \ the egress table. Used as an index to the VNET \ Voice Egress Digit Manipulation Configuration \ table. Configuration); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETEgressDigManipPhoneNum.name: nvmVNETEgressDigManipPhoneNum
nvmVNETEgressDigManipPhoneNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the phone \ number that voice channels are associated with. \ This is the number to be registered to the Address \ Server (RSA). (Configuration); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', and '*'.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETEgressDigManipString.name: nvmVNETEgressDigManipString
nvmVNETEgressDigManipString.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects commands \ to produce the egress digits for FXO, E&M, \ or FXS 3-Port interface. The result is the \ number to be sent to the connected phone \ device. (Configuration); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, '#', '*', \ '+', 'D', 'H', and 'I'. The character 'H' is \ used to trigger immediate dial handling by the PBX.; CAPABILITIES = ;

nvmVNETEgressDigManipChIDList.name: nvmVNETEgressDigManipChIDList
nvmVNETEgressDigManipChIDList.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects voice channels \ associated with the phone number. The valid \ string consists of the substring 'B1'~'B6', \ 'C1'~'C12', 'D1'~'D12', and 'E1'~'E2'. \ (Configuration); HELP = Valid characters are decimal digits, 'B', 'C', \ 'D', and 'E'.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusTable.name: mcmVNETChStatusTable
mcmVNETChStatusTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Channel Status Display table. \ HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETChStatusEntry.name: mcmVNETChStatusEntry
mcmVNETChStatusEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Channel Status Display \ table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusLimID.name: mcmVNETChStatusLimID
mcmVNETChStatusLimID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The card lim (logical interface module) number of \ a particular voice channel. Used as an index to \ the VNET Voice Channel Status Display table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusChannelID.name: mcmVNETChStatusChannelID
mcmVNETChStatusChannelID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The position of the voice channel in the lim. \ Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Channel Status Display table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusInterfaceType.name: mcmVNETChStatusInterfaceType
mcmVNETChStatusInterfaceType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the interface \ type of the specified voice channel.; HELP = Upon powerup, the interface type will not be \ available until the DSP software is loaded and its \ status is reported.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusInterfaceSwID.name: mcmVNETChStatusInterfaceSwID
mcmVNETChStatusInterfaceSwID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the command \ interface version ID (CIVID) of the specified voice \ channel. (Note: CIVID is 20 or above.); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusEMType.name: mcmVNETChStatusEMType
mcmVNETChStatusEMType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the E&M \ type of the specified voice channel.; HELP = This is for E&M interface channels only. Other \ interface types will show notApplicable.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusModelID.name: mcmVNETChStatusModelID
mcmVNETChStatusModelID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the hardware \ module type for the specified DVM voice channel.; HELP = This is for DVM voice channels only. Analog \ voice channels will show notApplicable.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusDSPOperation.name: mcmVNETChStatusDSPOperation
mcmVNETChStatusDSPOperation.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the current \ DSP status of the specified voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusNetworkConnect.name: mcmVNETChStatusNetworkConnect
mcmVNETChStatusNetworkConnect.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the current \ channel network connect status of the specified \ voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChHwType.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChHwType
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChHwType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the remote \ voice channel hardware type (corresponding to \ the specified voice channel).; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChNodeName.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChNodeName
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChNodeName.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the remote \ voice channel node name (corresponding to \ the specified voice channel).; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChNum.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChNum
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChNum.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the remote \ voice channel number (corresponding to \ the specified voice channel).; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChIfType.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChIfType
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChIfType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the remote \ voice channel interface type (corresponding to \ the specified voice channel).; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteFrameIfVer.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteFrameIfVer
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteFrameIfVer.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the final \ negotiated software version to be run on both \ sides of a voice channel connection.; HELP = This will be 0 if the specified \ voice channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChVoiceAlg.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChVoiceAlg
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChVoiceAlg.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the final \ negotiated voice algorithm running on both \ sides of a voice channel connection.; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChFaxAlg.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChFaxAlg
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChFaxAlg.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the final \ negotiated voice fax algorithm and maximum \ speed running on both sides of a voice fax \ channel connection.; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice fax channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChModemAlg.name: mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChModemAlg
mcmVNETChStatusRemoteChModemAlg.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the final \ negotiated voice modem algorithm and maximum \ speed running on both sides of a voice modem \ channel connection.; HELP = This will be the NULL string if the specified \ voice fax channel is not connected.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusSelfTestResult.name: mcmVNETChStatusSelfTestResult
mcmVNETChStatusSelfTestResult.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the results \ of a self test performed on the specified voice \ channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusFlashEPROM.name: mcmVNETChStatusFlashEPROM
mcmVNETChStatusFlashEPROM.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the current \ flash EPROM status in the DSP of the specified \ voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusEPROM.name: mcmVNETChStatusEPROM
mcmVNETChStatusEPROM.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the current \ EPROM status in the DSP of the specified voice \ channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusDspPROMVer.name: mcmVNETChStatusDspPROMVer
mcmVNETChStatusDspPROMVer.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the DSP PROM \ version of the specified voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusPROMID.name: mcmVNETChStatusPROMID
mcmVNETChStatusPROMID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the PROM \ ID of the specified voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatusInputLevel.name: mcmVNETChStatusInputLevel
mcmVNETChStatusInputLevel.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the input \ level of the specified voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

voiceSysStatusPhoneRegistrationStatus.name: voiceSysStatusPhoneRegistrationStatus
voiceSysStatusPhoneRegistrationStatus.description: NAME = PhoneRegistrationStatus; DESC = Indicates current communications \ status with NAS; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETChStatsTable.name: mcmVNETChStatsTable
mcmVNETChStatsTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The VNET Voice Channel Statistics Display table. \ HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmVNETChStatsEntry.name: mcmVNETChStatsEntry
mcmVNETChStatsEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the VNET Voice Channel Statistics \ Display table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsLimID.name: mcmVNETChStatsLimID
mcmVNETChStatsLimID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The card lim (logical interface module) number of a \ particular voice channel. Used as an index to the \ VNET Voice Channel Statistics Display table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsChannelID.name: mcmVNETChStatsChannelID
mcmVNETChStatsChannelID.description: NAME = ; DESC = The position of the voice channel in the lim. \ Used as an index to the VNET Voice \ Channel Statistics Display table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsOutCallConnTime.name: mcmVNETChStatsOutCallConnTime
mcmVNETChStatsOutCallConnTime.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ connection time (in sec) since the last statistics \ reset for the specified voice channel outgoing \ calls. (Excludes call setup time and local calls.) ; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsInCallConnTime.name: mcmVNETChStatsInCallConnTime
mcmVNETChStatsInCallConnTime.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ connection time (in sec) since the last statistics \ reset for the specified voice channel incoming \ calls. (Excludes local calls.) ; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsOutCallsSucceded.name: mcmVNETChStatsOutCallsSucceded
mcmVNETChStatsOutCallsSucceded.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ number of positive call responses sent from the \ remote DSP since the last statistics reset \ for the specified voice channel. (Excludes \ local calls.) ; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsOutCallsFailed.name: mcmVNETChStatsOutCallsFailed
mcmVNETChStatsOutCallsFailed.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ number of negative call responses sent from the \ remote DSP since the last statistics reset \ for the specified voice channel. (Excludes \ local calls.) ; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsInCallsAccepted.name: mcmVNETChStatsInCallsAccepted
mcmVNETChStatsInCallsAccepted.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ number of positive call responses sent to the \ remote DSP since the last statistics reset \ for the specified voice channel. (Excludes \ local calls.) ; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsInCallsRejected.name: mcmVNETChStatsInCallsRejected
mcmVNETChStatsInCallsRejected.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ number of negative call responses sent to the \ remote DSP since the last statistics reset \ for the specified voice channel. (Excludes \ local calls.) ; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChStatsNumberOfResets.name: mcmVNETChStatsNumberOfResets
mcmVNETChStatsNumberOfResets.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the total \ number of resets sent to the DSP corresponding \ to the specified voice channel.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETChControlActionCmd.name: mcmVNETChControlActionCmd
mcmVNETChControlActionCmd.description: NAME = ; DESC = Setting this object will perform various \ actions on the specified voice channel. \ Note: Starting with software release 3.0, \ the enumeration clearChannelCounters (2) is \ not supported. The enumeration is included \ here only to support backwards compatibility \ for software versions prior to release 3.0.; HELP = 1: perform hardware reset to DSP. \ 2: clear statistics counter. \ 3: download code to DSP. \ 4: disconnect call. \ 5: set DSP to loopback mode. \ 6: terminate test. \ 7: force connect channel by using the \ auto call number. NOTE: This option is not \ supported by the ISDN BRI voice card.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmVNETSysControlActionCmd.name: mcmVNETSysControlActionCmd
mcmVNETSysControlActionCmd.description: NAME = ; DESC = Setting this object will perform various \ actions on the VNET voice system. \ Note: Starting with software release 3.0, \ the enumerations clearNetworkCounters (1) and \ clearChannelCounters (3) are not supported. \ The enumeration is included here only to support \ backwards compatibility for software versions \ prior to release 3.0.; HELP = 1: clear network statistics counters. \ 2: perform hardware reset to all channels. \ 3: clear all channel statistics counters. \ 4: download code to all channels. \ 5: disconnect all channel's calls. \ 6: set all channels to loopback mode. \ 7: terminate all channel's tests. \ 8: force connect all channels by using the auto call numbers. NOTE: This option is not \ supported by the ISDN BRI voice card.; \ 9: re-register phone number.; CAPABILITIES = NET_OPER, VPN_OPER ;
